  .diagram-box { background: #f8fafc; border: 2px solid #d0dde8; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; font-family: 'Consolas', monospace; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.4; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Observer Pattern Refactoring Report</h1>
<div class="header-info">
  <strong>Project:</strong> Website Monitoring System &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  <strong>Date:</strong> June 10, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  <strong>Pattern:</strong> Observer (Behavioral)
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>1. Problem with the Original Design</h2>
<p>
  The original code used a <strong>polling-based</strong> approach. The <code>MonitoringSystem</code> class had two methods — <code>checkUpdate()</code> and <code>triggerNotification()</code> — that manually iterated over every user, every subscription, and every website to detect changes and dispatch notifications. This created several problems:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Tight coupling:</strong> <code>MonitoringSystem</code> was tightly coupled to <code>User</code>, <code>Subscription</code>, and <code>Website</code>, orchestrating all update logic centrally.</li>
  <li><strong>Polling overhead:</strong> The system had to be explicitly asked to check for updates, even when nothing changed.</li>
  <li><strong>Fragile notification logic:</strong> The <code>boolean[]</code> array approach for tracking which users had updates was index-dependent and error-prone.</li>
  <li><strong>Violation of Open/Closed Principle:</strong> Adding new observer types (e.g., an admin dashboard) would require modifying <code>MonitoringSystem</code>.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>2. Observer Pattern Solution</h2>
<p>
  The Observer pattern establishes a one-to-many dependency: when a <code>Website</code> (Subject) changes state, all registered <code>Subscription</code> objects (Observers) are notified automatically.
</p>

<div class="diagram-box">
        &laquo;interface&raquo;                  &laquo;interface&raquo;
          Subject ◄──────────────────── Observer
   + addObserver(Observer)            + update(Website)
   + removeObserver(Observer)                ▲
   + notifyObservers()                       │
          ▲                                  │
          │ implements                       │ implements
          │                                  │
      Website ─────── notifies ──────► Subscription
   - observers: List&lt;Observer&gt;        - owner: User
   - currentContent: String           - website: Website
   + updateContent(String)            + update(Website)
   + addObserver(Observer)            + create(Website)
   + removeObserver(Observer)         + cancel()
   + notifyObservers()
</div>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>3. File Changes Summary</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>File</th><th>Status</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Observer.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-new">NEW</span></td><td>Observer interface with <code>update(Website)</code> method</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Subject.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-new">NEW</span></td><td>Subject interface with <code>addObserver</code>, <code>removeObserver</code>, <code>notifyObservers</code></td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Website.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-modified">MODIFIED</span></td><td>Implements <code>Subject</code>; auto-notifies observers on content change</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Subscription.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-modified">MODIFIED</span></td><td>Implements <code>Observer</code>; reacts to website updates automatically</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>MonitoringSystem.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-modified">MODIFIED</span></td><td>Removed <code>checkUpdate()</code> and <code>triggerNotification()</code> (no longer needed)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Main.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-modified">MODIFIED</span></td><td>Simplified — no manual polling calls; just update content directly</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>User.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-unchanged">UNCHANGED</span></td><td>No changes needed</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>Notification.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-unchanged">UNCHANGED</span></td><td>No changes needed</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>NotificationPreference.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-unchanged">UNCHANGED</span></td><td>No changes needed</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>SubscriptionStatus.java</code></td><td><span class="badge-unchanged">UNCHANGED</span></td><td>No changes needed</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>4. Detailed Changes</h2>

<h3>4.1 New: Observer.java</h3>
<pre><code>public interface Observer {
    void update(Website website);
}</code></pre>
<p>Defines the contract for any object that wants to be notified when a <code>Website</code> changes.</p>

<h3>4.2 New: Subject.java</h3>
<pre><code>public interface Subject {
    void addObserver(Observer observer);
    void removeObserver(Observer observer);
    void notifyObservers();
}</code></pre>
<p>Defines the contract for observable objects that maintain a list of observers.</p>

<h3>4.3 Modified: Website.java</h3>
<p>Key changes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Implements <code>Subject</code> interface</li>
  <li>Maintains a <code>List&lt;Observer&gt; observers</code></li>
  <li><code>updateContent()</code> now automatically calls <code>notifyObservers()</code> when content changes, then syncs the cache</li>
  <li>Removed <code>isUpdate()</code> — change detection is now internal to <code>updateContent()</code></li>
</ul>
<pre><code>// Before (polling-based):
public boolean isUpdate() {
    String latestContent = fetchContent();
    if (!latestContent.equals(cachedContent)) return true;
    return false;
}

// After (push-based):
public void updateContent(String contentUpdated) {
    this.currentContent = contentUpdated;
    if (!currentContent.equals(cachedContent)) {
        notifyObservers();                    // push to all observers
        this.cachedContent = currentContent;  // sync cache
    }
}</code></pre>

<h3>4.4 Modified: Subscription.java</h3>
<p>Key changes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Implements <code>Observer</code> interface</li>
  <li><code>create(Website)</code> now calls <code>web.addObserver(this)</code> to register</li>
  <li>New <code>update(Website)</code> method handles incoming notifications automatically</li>
  <li><code>cancel()</code> now calls <code>website.removeObserver(this)</code> to unregister</li>
</ul>
<pre><code>// Observer callback — called automatically by Website
@Override
public void update(Website website) {
    if (this.status == SubscriptionStatus.ACTIVE) {
        String mess = "The Website with " + website.getUrlWebsite() + " is updated";
        Notification notif = new Notification(notifications.size(), mess);
        notif.generate(website.getUrlWebsite());
        addNotification(notif);
    }
}</code></pre>

<h3>4.5 Modified: MonitoringSystem.java</h3>
<p>Removed methods:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>checkUpdate(List&lt;User&gt;)</code> — no longer needed; websites push updates</li>
  <li><code>triggerNotification(boolean[])</code> — no longer needed; subscriptions handle their own notifications</li>
</ul>
<p>The class now serves purely as a registry for users and websites.</p>

<h3>4.6 Modified: Main.java</h3>
<pre><code>// Before:
boolean[] isUpdates = system.checkUpdate(system.getListUsers());
system.triggerNotification(isUpdates);
amazon.updateContent("The sales is on July 28th");
isUpdates = system.checkUpdate(system.getListUsers());
system.triggerNotification(isUpdates);

// After:
amazon.updateContent("The sales is on July 28th");  // observers notified automatically</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>5. Benefits of the Refactoring</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>Before</th><th>After</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Coupling</td><td>MonitoringSystem orchestrates everything</td><td>Website and Subscription communicate directly via interfaces</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Notification trigger</td><td>Manual polling: <code>checkUpdate()</code> + <code>triggerNotification()</code></td><td>Automatic: <code>updateContent()</code> pushes to observers</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Extensibility</td><td>New observer types require modifying MonitoringSystem</td><td>Any class implementing <code>Observer</code> can subscribe</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Lifecycle</td><td>No cleanup on cancellation</td><td><code>cancel()</code> unregisters from the subject</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Code in MonitoringSystem</td><td>~30 lines of polling/notification logic</td><td>0 lines — removed entirely</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

</body>
</html>
